	<text id="ruskin_to_mother_july_16_1867">
	    
	    <header>
	        <inventNo>1996L00317</inventNo>
	    </header>
	
	    <body>
	        <div type="text">
	            <pb n="1"/>           
	            <opener>
	                <placeName><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="Q1017196" type="place">Wigtown,</rs>
	                </placeName>
	                <day>Tuesday morning,</day>
	                <date when="1867-07-16"><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs type="date">16th July, 67.</rs>
	                </date>
	                <salute>My dearest <rs key="47637407" type="person">Mother</rs>,</salute><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	            </opener>
	            
	            <p id="p1">
	                <s id="s1">I was detained by weather yesterday, but am really off this morning, and hope to send you telegram from <rs key="Q1025076" type="place">Keswick</rs> to-morrow, as soon, almost, as you can get this.</s>
	            </p>    
	
	            <p id="p2">    
	                <s id="s2">I have given great pleasure by coming here, and I know several conditions of things respecting the family which enabled me to judge more clearly in what regards <rs key="p_la_touche" type="person">Percy</rs>.</s>
	            </p>    
	
	            <p id="p3">    
	                <s id="s3">That was what I mainly came for</s>
	                <s id="s4">I think more highly of <pb n="2"/> <rs key="76205504" type="person">Joanna</rs> and her sister than I did, nor am I disappointed in thier way of life - as compared with all around them: but there is much to depress me in the aspect of <rs key="Q22" type="place">Scotland</rs> and in the desertion of these provincial towns - and I have the secret of extracting sadness from all things - instead of joys which is no enviable talisman.</s>
	            </p>    
	
	            <p id="p4">    
	                <s id="s5">Forgive me if I ever write in a way that may pain you - </s>
	                <s id="s6">It is best that you should know when I write cheerfully <pb n="3"/> it is no pretended cheerfulness - so when I am sad - I think it right to confess it.</s>
	            </p>
	            
	            <closer>
	                <salute>Ever my dearest <rs key="47637407" type="person">Mother</rs>, Your most affectionate Son,</salute><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary -->
	                <signed><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="73859585" type="person">J. Ruskin.</rs>
	                </signed>
	             </closer>
	
	        </div>
	    </body>
	</text>      
	
